	* src/atm_funcs.cc (e_eq_ice): Added this function. It calculates
	the equilibrium water vapor pressure over ice.
	
	* src/atm_funcs.cc (e_eq_water): Added this function. It calculates
	the equilibrium water vapor pressure over liquid water.
	

2003-12-08  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-145

	* src/continua.cc (MPM93RainExt), src/m_wfs.cc (absloswfs_rte_limb):
	Initialize variable with 0 which might be used uninitialized.

	NOTE: The warning about variables that are probably used uninitialized
	is only displayed with enabled optimizations because the information
	about the used variables is determined by the compiler's optimizer.

2003-12-08  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-144

	* autogen.sh: Sync with arts 1.1.

	* configure.in: Sync with arts 1.1.
	Added wfs_spectro_example.arts to AC_OUTPUT.

	* COPYING: Updated.

	* doc/examples/wfs_spectro_example.arts: Removed.

	* doc/examples/wfs_spectro_example.arts.in: Added. Replaced absolute
	paths to arts-data with @ac_arts_data@.

	* doc/examples/Makefile.am: Added wfs_spectro_example.arts*.

	* src/methods.h (operator=): Removed name of dummy parameter.

	* src/make_auto_md_cc.cc (main): Omit name for unused function
	parameters. Backported from arts 1.1.

	* src/continua.cc (PWR98H2OAbsModel), (XINT_FUN), (CKD_222_self_h2o),
	(CKD_222_foreign_h2o), (CKD_242_self_h2o), (CKD_242_foreign_h2o),
	(CKD_mt_100_self_h2o), (CKD_mt_100_foreign_h2o), (CKD_241_co2),
	(CKD_mt_co2), (CKD_mt_CIArot_n2), (CKD_mt_CIAfun_n2),
	(CKD_mt_CIAfun_o2), (CKD_mt_v0v0_o2), (CKD_mt_v1v0_o2),
	(PWR93O2AbsModel), (Standard_O2_continuum), (MPM93_N2_continuum),
	(MPM93RainExt), (addspec_), (artsckd_), (swv24_), (swv_mpmf87s93__):
	Commented out all unused parameters and variables. Put a FIXME in
	commented lines.
	Initialize member fill_3 of struct n2part_ with 0 to avoid warning.
	Fixed initialization of structures in f2c to fix gcc2 warning
	'aggregate has a partly bracketed initializer'. f2c sucks.

	* src/lineshapes.cc (lineshape_no_shape), (lineshape_lorentz),
	(lineshape_doppler), (lineshape_CO2_lorentz),
	(lineshape_norm_no_norm), (lineshape_norm_linear),
	(lineshape_norm_quadratic): Commented out names of unused parameters.
	(lineshape_norm_quadratic): Removed unused constant PI.

	* src/m_abs.cc (AtmFromRaw): Removed unused variable species_data.

	* src/m_hdf.cc (binfile_read1), (binfile_read2), (binfile_read3):
	Commented out unused parameter filename.

	* src/m_io.cc (VectorWriteAscii): Removed static_cast.
	(VectorSetLengthFromVector), (VectorPressuresForLinAltitudes),
	(VectorPlanck), (VectorMatrixMultiply), (MatrixMatrixMultiply),
	(MatrixMatrixAdd): Commented out names of unused parameters.

	* src/m_los.cc (los_refraction), (zaFromZtan), (zaFromDeltat):
	Commented out names of unused parameters.
	Include cmath instead of math.h.

	* src/m_wfs.cc (sourceloswfs), (kb_spectro), (kSpectro),
	(kCalibration), (kxAllocate): Commented out names of unused parameters.

	* src/m_method_list.cc (MethodListDefine): Commented out name of
	unused parameter.

	* src/matpackI.h (Range::Range): Comment out name of unused Joker
	parameter in two constructors.

	* src/test_matpack.cc (test10): Replaced static_cast by cast to const
	Vector.

2003-12-05  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-143

	* src/m_los.cc (CoolingRates): Fixed a bug put in last minute
	before last commit. Integer abs was used instead of fabs, which
	resulted in that step lenght always was set to 10 km (which was
	the hard-coded upper limit. I think the abs problem appeared when
	using an older compiler (but not sure).

	The upper limit for l_step is now a keyword argument.

	The results show now excellent agreement with Clough and Iacomo,
	JGR, 1995. I would say that the cooling rate implementation is
	verified and works.

	* src/methods.cc: Wrote online documentation for CoolingRates. 

	* doc/uguide/rte.tex: Wrote down description of cooling rate 
	calculations. Mainly copied from ACECLIM MTR report.

2003-12-03  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-142

	* src/m_los.cc (CoolingRates): It seems that the cooling rates
	calculations now work. Obtained test results are very close to
	what reported by Clough et al 1995, but only a narrow band has been
	tested.

	The WSM is called CoolingRates. Two new WSV are introduced: coolrate
	and p_coolrate.

	Documentation for CoolingRates is so far missing. Will be written.

2003-12-03  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-141

	* src/m_los.cc (CoolingRates): A quick commit, to get a backup. More
	details later. The function is not yet working properly.

