2003-11-21  Thomas Kuhn <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-134

	* src/continua.cc: check of the CKD model implementations for the
	versions 2.2.2, 2.4.2, and MT.1.00. A IDL toos is developed to
	make the check on the basis of the absorption coefficients
	calculated by the original F77 code and by the arts-CKD
	implementation. This IDL tool is a separate cvs package
	called "arts_abs_model_implementation_check".
	
2003-10-23  Thomas Kuhn <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-133

	* src/continua.cc (CKD_241_co2): implementation of CKDv2.4.1 CO2
	continuum absorption. This CKD CO2 continuum is the same as 
	CKD_MT_1.00 with the only exception of the missing increase by a
	factor of 7 in the frequency interval 500 to 900 cm^-1. The
	corresponding tag name of the CKDv2.4.1 CO2 cont. abs. is 'CO2-CKD241'.

2003-10-09  Thomas Kuhn <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-132

	* src/continua.cc (XINT_FUN): bug fix for the interpolation of
	the CKD continua. Now the previously detected discontinuous steps
	are removewd. Checks showed no such steps anymore.

2003-10-08  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-131

	* src/m_abs (lines_per_tgCompact): Reimplemented deletion of line
	records. Instead of erasing every single element, build a new list and
	copy it over the old one. Otherwise the whole ArrayOfLineRecord is
	copied once for each erase which actually kills performance (slow down
	by three-digit factor).

2003-09-30  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-130

	* src/m_abs.cc (lines_per_tgCreateFromLines): Moved warning about
	transitions of e.g. isotopes neglected from out0 to out2.  This as
	in some cases you neglect such lines but want ARTS to be silent.

