2003-09-08  Christian Melsheimer  <melsheimer@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-125

	* aii/aii_writedatum.pro: applied a 'strcompress' to ouput of 
	systime; otherwise the double blank between month name and single
	digit days (e.g., Sep  8) messed up the result.

	* aii/aii_aa_read_general.pro, aii/aii_checks.pro,
	aii/aii_color_table.pro, aii/aii_compile.pro,
	aii/aii_get_hostname.pro, aii/aii_klegend_d.pro,
	aii/aii_plotsymbols.pro, aii/aii_readfile.pro,
	aii/aii_startup.pro, aii/aii_student_t_dist_table.pro,
	aii/aii_where_str.pro, aii/aii_writedatum.pro,
	aii/CreateArtsControlFile.pro, aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro,
	aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro, aii/plot_RT_1.pro,
	aii/plot_trans_1.pro, aii/plot_vmr_per_tg.pro,
	aii/read_artsvar.pro, aii/read_datafile.pro,
	aii/read_tag_groups.pro, aii/showme.pro, aii/sort_abs_2.pro,
	aii/sort_abs.pro, aii/WaterVaporSatPressure.pro,
	aii/write_artsvar.pro, aii/write_datafile.pro
	aii/WVContParamFit.pro:
	Inserted one line containing just ';+' and one line containing just
	';-' before/after the descriptive comments of routines in each file
	(also slightly extended some descriptions).  This way, the idl
	routines doc_library and mk_html_help can read the info and
	display it.
	If you type, in IDL, e.g.:
       	 doc_library,'aii_read_general' 
	the lines between ';+' and ';-' will be displayed on your IDL console.
	If you type
	 mk_html_help,'<path-to-arts>/aii','help.html'
	
	(of course replace <path-to-arts> with the path to arts!), a nice
	documentation in html format of all idl programs in the 'aii'
	directory will be written to the file help.html.  If there is a
	line containing ';NAME:' the following line is taken as the name of
	the routine. Therefore I changed ';Name:' and ';name:' into ;NAME:
	where necessary.  Look up 'mk_html_help' in IDL online help to
	know more...

	* aii/aii_startup.pro: Added a line to generate HTML documentation
	of procedures/functions in aii; documentation will be written to
	'aii_help.html' 

	* aii/.cvsignore: added aii_help.html

2003-09-08  Sho Tsujimaru <sho@sat.physik.uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-124

	* ami/retrieval/opt_fmono.m: Added. 
	
2003-09-07  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-123

	* src/constants.cc: Added HZ2CM.

	* src/lineshapes.cc: Added the lineshapes CO2_Lorentz and
	CO2_Drayson. These lineshapes are an emprical way to consider line
	mixing and finite duration of collision in the line wings. This
	means that the finer details in the line centre of line mixing are
	not covered. This line shape shall not be combined with any
	cut-off, normalisation factor or continua.

	The Cousin chi factors used, were obtained for the v3 band (2600
	cm-1), but these chi factors are also frequently applied for v2
	(650 cm-1). 

	The temperature dependency of the chi factor is not implemented as
	I could not understand how to pass the temperature to the function
	calculating the line shape. The chi factors are valid for 238 K.

	* src/m_io.cc (NumericCopyLastOfVector): Added this WSM.

	* src/m_abs.cc (xsec_per_tgAddLines): Commented out part that gave
	an incorrect message of total number of transitions to do. The
	part shall now give correct messages if uncommented.

2003-08-29  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-122

	* doc/uguide/absorption.tex: just small corrections for a few 
	isotopic ratios.

2003-08-29  Thomas Kuhn  <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-121

	* src/continua.cc: added some continua from the newest CKD version
	(CKD_MT version 1.00, see http://www.rtweb.aer.com/continuum_frame.html).
	 - H2O foreign continuum (0-20000 cm^-1, tag="H2O-ForeignContCKDMT100")
	 - H2O self continuum (0-20000 cm^-1, tag="H2O-SelfContCKDMT100")
	 - CO2 far wing continuum (0-10000 cm^-1, tag="CO2-CKDMT100")
	   This continuum is just the far wing contribution of the CO2
	   lines in the many bands. Normally the line shape used for CO2
	   has a cutoff of 25cm^-1. Thus this continuum adjusts the CO2 
	   absorption in the far wing to the measured level. One has to
	   keep in mind that this procedure is strongly empirical!
	 - N2 collision induced absorption rotational band (0-350 cm^-1,  
	   tag="N2-CIArotCKDMT100")
	   CKD takes it from the Borysow & Frommhold model and brings it
	   into the usual CKD format. The reference is
	   Borysow, A, and L. Frommhold, 
           Collision-induced rototranslational absorption spectra of N2-N2
           pairs for temperatures from 50 to 300K, The Astrophysical
	   Journal, 311, 1043-1057, 1986.
	 - N2 collision induced absorption fundamental band
	   (2085-2670 cm^-1, tag="N2-CIAfunCKDMT100")
           CKD takes it from Lafferty et al. model and brings it
	   into the usual CKD format. The reference is
	   Lafferty, W.J., A.M. Solodov,A. Weber, W.B. Olson and 
           J._M. Hartmann, Infrared collision-induced absorption by 
           N2 near 4.3 microns for atmospheric applications: 
           Measurements and emprirical modeling, Appl. Optics, vol.35, 
           pp.5911-5917, 1996
	 - O2 collision induced absorption fundamental band (1340-1850
	   cm^-1, , tag="O2-CIAfunCKDMT100")
	   CKD takes it from  Thibault et al. model and brings it
	   into the usual CKD format. The reference is
           F. Thibault, V. Menoux, R. Le Doucen, L. Rosenman, 
           J.-M. Hartmann, Ch. Boulet, Infrared collision-induced
	   absorption by O2 near 6.4 microns for atmospheric applications:
           measurements and emprirical modeling, Appl. Optics, vol.35,
	   pp.5911-5917, 1996.
	 - O2 v0 <-- v0 absorption band (7536-8500 cm^-1, tag="O2-v0v0CKDMT100")
	   CKD takes it from  Mate et al. and Mlawer et al. model and 
	   brings it into the usual CKD format. The reference is
           B. Mate, C. Lugez, G.T. Fraser, W.J. Lafferty,
           Absolute Intensities for the O2 1.27 micron continuum absorption,  
           J. Geophys. Res., 104, 30,585-30,590, 1999
	   and
	   Mlawer, Clough, Brown, Stephen, Landry, Goldman, Murcray,
           Observed  Atmospheric Collision Induced Absorption in Near 
	   Infrared Oxygen Bands, J. Geophys. Res., vol.103, no.D4, 
	   pp.3859-3863, 1998.
	 - O2 v1 <-- v0 absorption band (9100-11000 cm^-1, tag="O2-v1v0CKDMT100")
           CKD takes it from  Mlawer et al. model and brings it 
	   into the usual CKD format. The reference is
	   Mlawer, Clough, Brown, Stephen, Landry, Goldman, Murcray,
           Observed  Atmospheric Collision Induced Absorption in Near 
	   Infrared Oxygen Bands, J. Geophys. Res., vol.103, no.D4, 
	   pp.3859-3863, 1998.
        For the arts tag names see doc/examples/cont_example.arts. A
        detailed documentation in the uguide will follow.

	* aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro: modification in the way thew y-axis
	range is determined and about the plot title.
	
2003-08-28  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-120

	* src/species_data.cc: updated the isotopic ratio values taken from
	HITRAN96, with the ones from HITRAN00. The differences are very
	small. A intercomparison of the two datasets showed that only some
	isotopic ratios in HITRAN00 were given with a higher
	precision. E.g., for CO2-636 the old value was 0.01106 while the
	new value is 0.0110574.

	* src/partition_function_data.cc: a small correction according the
	species_data.cc file. 

	* doc/uguide/absorption.tex: updated the table listing the species
	implemented and the isotopic ratios according to the new updates
	included in species_data.cc. Now all the species, continua, and 
	clouds, are consistently listed in tables. 

