	ybatchFromRadiosonde (finegrid=0).

2003-08-06  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-117

	* src/math_funcs.cc (interp_lin_vector): Interpolation works now
	also for new grid points just outside the original grid range.
	(interp_lin_matrix): Interpolation works now also for new grid
	points just outside the original grid range.
	(interp_check): Now Tolerates the new grid to extend half a grid
	distance outside the original grid.

2003-07-30  Thomas Kuhn <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-116

	* src/absorption.c: added the 'microwave approximation' line
	intensity for the case when the line shape normalization is
	'quadratic'. Now the line intensity and the quadratic
	normalization together correspond to the so called 'microwave
	approximation' as described by P. Rosenkranz in the Janssen book
	in chapter 2, equation 2.16. Some comparisons are performed with
	this new abs calculation against the newly implemented VVH
	option. the difference is very small in the microwave range - as
	expected. Hence the advice is to use generally the option VVH for
	the line absorption at any frequency so you are sure that the
	calculation is made in a theoretically correct way.

2003-07-30  Axel von_Engeln  <engeln@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-115

	* src/m_los: some bugfixes with sourcetransyCalcSaveMemory.

