2003-07-28  Axel von_Engeln  <engeln@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-104

	* src/absorption.h, absorption.cc, lineshapes.cc: added
	temperature to lineshape normalization factor. Added new
	normalization factor VVH, based on the normalization to the
	Van-Vleck Huber lineshape. This should be the correct norm for IR
	calculations if using HITRAN similar catalogues.

	* m_abs.cc: typo removed

2003-07-25  Axel von_Engeln  <engeln@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-103

	* aii/aii_compile: moved to aii_compile.pro, thus is found in IDL
	path

	* aii/aii_startup: moved to aii_startup.pro, thus is found in IDL
	path. Modified slightly the device font

	* aii/myregress.pro: added, TKS routine missing in aii directory.

	* aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro: implemented um keyword for frequeny
	range in um, removed some unnecessary for loops, removed explicit
	settings of system variables, plotting part simplified, legend
	modified 

	* aux/part_fct/partition_function.pro: included the possibility to
	interpolate partition fcts in ln coordinates, as suggested by
	D. Feist during Bredbeck. This first quick hack shows better
	results in linear space.

	* src/constants.cc: added EARTH_EQUATORIAL_RADIUS and
	EARTH_POLAR_RADIUS. along these lines: it seems strange that the
	EARTH_RADIUS itself is almost the equatorial one, shouldn't that
	be a mean one?

	* src/m_abs.cc: added:
	- hseSetFromLatitude, calculates gravity in hse vector following
	international gravity formula. 
	- hseSetFromLatitudeIndex, requires p_abs, z_abs and sets hse vector
	entries pref, zref according to index, thus more flexible than
	hseFromBottom. Otherwise as hseSetFromLatitude.

	* src/methods.cc: see src/m_abs.cc

	* src/atm_funcs.cc, atm_funcs.h: added g_of_lat, calculates gravity using
	international gravity formula as function of lat.

