2003-07-16  Viju O.-J.  <vojohn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-94

	* doc/examples/radiosonde_example.arts: Updated the example
	control file.

2003-07-16  Viju O.-J.  <vojohn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-93		
	
	* src/m_batch.cc (ybatchFromRadiosonde): Modified this method to
	use a finer grid for absorption calculation. Added a keyword
	parameter *finegrid*.
	
	There are two options now:
	1. set keyword finegrid = 0
		The calculations will be the same as before. Absorption
	is calculated on the radiosonde levels. But now the conversion of
	radiance to Planck brightness temperature is done inside this
	function. This should be changed in the control file.

	2. set keyword finegrid = 1
		The absorption is calculated on a very fine grid of about
	15 m spacing. *p_abs* grid goes only up to 100 hPa so that there is
	no atmosphere above 100 hPa. This is equivalent to cut the
	profiles at 100 hPa. If a profile does not reach up to 100 hPa
	calculation is not done for this profile and -1 is put as the
	value of brightness temperature. Please note that *l_step* should
	be less than 15 m, say for example 5 m. Conversion from radiance
	to brightness temperature should be removed from the control file.

	* src/methods.cc (define_md_data): Added keyword parameter and
	updated the documentation.	
	
2003-07-01  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-92

	* src/arts.h: Minor doc update.

2003-07-01  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-91

	* doc/doxygen/Makefile.am: Copy arts logo to html dir.

	* src/arts.h: Updated doxygen main page with logo and Claudia's
	arts description from the satpage.

2003-06-27  Christian Melsheimer  <melsheimer@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-90

	* aii/aii_plot_file.pro:  
	In line 322, set YOFFS from 0.0 to 29.6 to make plot appear on the
	actual A4 area (and not somewhere outside because of negative bounding
	box values);
	* aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro:  
	modified lines 407-412 such that abstotal[] is really the sum of
	absorption by all tags;
	in line 536, passed the whole array of strings (charlegendarray)
	to aii_plot_legend, otherwise an error occurs for plotsum=1
	(i.e. when the total absorption is plotted in addition to the
	absorption per tag).

