2003-04-08  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-74

	* src/m_wfs.cc: modification made in kSpectro function. Now, it outputs
	the matrix given the spectroscopic parameters uncertainty
	(*.SS.aa) and the correlation matrix (*.Mcorr.aa). The assumed
	correlation is input parameter (given in control file).
	The two outputs are very useful to calculate the spectroscopic error.
	
	* methods.cc: modified according to new syntax

	* workspace.cc: included the workspace variable for S_S and Mcorr
	matrices. 

	* doc/example: included wfs_spectro_example.arts arts control file
	to exemplify the calculation of spectroscopic parameter WFs.

	* doc/uguide/wfuns_atm.tex: included a small section for
	spectroscopic parameters WFs.

2003-04-03  Thomas Kuhn  <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-73

	* aii/WaterVaporSatPressure.pro: update, make PTOT as optional
	input parameter. If no moist air correction is applied then PTOT
	is not required but if the moist air correction is invoced by
	corr='yes' then the total atmosperic pressure MUST be provided
	otherwise the default value of es is given back 
	(i.e. es = -9.99999e9). An example how the total pressure can be
	provided is to set the keyword PTOT to PTOT=1010.0E0.

2003-04-03  Thomas Kuhn  <tkuhn@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-72

	* aii/aii_startup: added this aii startup batch file which is
	similar to IDL_STARTUP just for ARTS/aii purposes
	* aii/aii_compile: compiles all the functions and procedures of
	the aii directory. Called by aii_startup. This ensures that all
	the functions/procedures are available to the user in the IDL session. 
	* aii/WaterVaporSatPressure.pro:  update of the water vapor
	saturation pressure calculation according to the formula of
	D. Sonntag, Meteorologische Zeitschrift, 1994 (Eq. 7, 8, 22, 23) 
	* aii/RH_test.pro: add this procedure to compare different
	saturation pressure calculations 
	* aii/RH_test_batch: batch file for RH_test.pro.
	* aii/aii_aa_read_general.pro: update of this procedure 
	* aii/aii_plot_file.pro: update of this procedure and in the same 
	file you find to small and simple functions which allows the user
	to open and close a postscript file for IDL plots.  
	* aii/aii_readfile.pro: separated this previously existing
	procedure into a separate file.
	* aii/aii_where_str.pro : separated this previously existing
	procedure into a separate file.
	* aii/aii_writedatum.pro: creats a string with the actual datum.
	* aii/plot_RT_1.pro: updated this procedure
	* aii/plot_abs_per_tg.pro: separated the aii_readfile procedure
	from this file.
	* aii/plot_abs_per_tg_2.pro: update of the input variables
	* aii/plot_vmr_per_tg.pro: updated the relative humidity calculation.
	* aii/read_tag_groups.pro: increasaed the hardcoded parameter
	which counts the separators of the tags.
	* aii/showme.pro: updated the input variable checks and call of 
	plot_abs_per_tg_2.
	* aii/showmebatch: add this idl batch file which calls showme.pro
	(has to be adjusted by each user)

