2002-12-03  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-55

	* ami/arts/arts_version.m: Added this function. It returns a string
	describing the ARTS version used.

2002-11-15  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-54

	* src/absorption.h
	* src/absorption.cc
	* Added new fields to LineRecord to read into spectroscopic
	parameters accuracies. For the moment the uncertainties are stored
	in Hz for the line position, and in relative difference for the
	other parameters ( such as line intensity, pressure broadening
	parameters, and pressure shift). The fields for the spectroscopic
	uncertainties are implemented for all available catalogs: HITRAN,
	MYTRAN, JPL, and ARTS. The old ARTS catalogs are also valid. If an
	uncertainty is missing then this is set to -1 (thanks to Stefan
	suggestion). 
	
	Added functions: 
 	- convHitranIERF: convert HITRAN index for frequency accuracy, to
	 accuracy in ARTS units (Hz). 
	 - convHitranIERFSH: convert HITRAN index for intensity and
	halfwidth, to accuracy in ARTS units (relative difference).
	- convMytranIER: convert MYTRAN index for the intensity and
	halfwidth accuracy to ARTS units (relative difference). 
     
2002-11-13  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-53
	
	* src/absorption.h: removed a small bug (sorry!)
	
2002-11-13  Carmen Verdes  <cverdes@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-52
	
	* src/absorption.h	
	* src/atm_funcs.cc
	* src/m_abs.cc
	* src/m_wfs.cc
	* src/methods.cc
	* (kbSpectro): Added a new function to calculate the spectroscopic
	parameters weighting function. This function should be able to
	calculate the weighting function for the line intensity, line
	position, pressure broadening parameters, and pressure shift. A
	do field is specified for each parameters: 0 means that no
	weighting function calculation is performed, 1 means that the
	weighting function for the corresponding parameters is performed.
	More documentation about this has to be added in the user guide.
	
2002-11-13  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-51

	* src/absorption.cc (ReadFromMytran2Stream): Fixed stray ")"
	bug. (Thanks to Carmen and Patrick for noticing this.)

2002-11-12  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-50

	* src/absorption.h: 
	* src/absorption.cc: 
	Removed a bad bug. So far the partition function value at the
	intensity reference temperature was pre-calculated, and stored
	amongst the species data. This was a logical error, because the
	reference temperature can be different for each line. In this case
	the program so far gave wrong results (only the reference
	temperature of the last line read was used). Nobody has noticed
	this, because in the catalogue files we used, the intensity
	reference temperature was always the same for all lines of the
	same species.

	Also added a lot of FIXMEs together with Carmen, concerning the
	implementation of accuracy fields in the ARTS internal line
	catalogue. 

2002-10-21  Patrick Eriksson  <Patrick.Eriksson@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-49

	* ami/hmatrix/hBinfile.m: Fixed two bugs reported by the Bern group.
	Many thanks Beat and Danial for reporting and finding the bugs.
	
	The function name inside the file was wrong. Added data type when
	reading bdata. 

