	t_abs contains only positive values. Otherwise throw runtime
	error.

2002-08-26  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-43
	
	* src/atm_funcs.cc (invrayjean): Integrated the calculation of
	SPEED_OF_LIGHT*SPEED_OF_LIGHT/(2*BOLTZMAN_CONST) into the for-loop
	and changed the order of the terms to avoid numerical
	instabilities. On Sun the above calculations leads to inf.

2002-08-23  Patrick Eriksson  <patrick@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-42

	* src/m_wfs.cc (kTemp): Removed some incorrect checks of the input.
	The check gave an incorrect error when there was propagation paths
	going outside the atmosphere.

2002-08-20  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de> (working under Arashs account)

	* arts-1-0-41

	* src/absorption.cc (xsec_species): Fixed yet another bug: The aux
	variable was too small by 1. This lead to a crash in the VoigtKunz
	lineshape functions.

2002-08-14  Patrick Eriksson  <patrick@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-40

	* ami/file/vtag2arts.data: O-6 was missing in the file.

	* ami/file/get_artsconfig.m: Extracts a configuration setting for arts.

	* ami/init.m: The init script now automatically adds the top folder
	of arts-data to the search path (to use the function arts_data_path).
	The information is taken from arts/config.h. Fancy, or?

	* ami/file/arts_path.m: Created this function to obtain the path to
	the arts top folder.

	* ami/file/cira86.m: Created this function that returns CIRA 
	temperatures and altitudes for arbitrary month, latitude and pressure.

	* ami/physics/zpot2zgeom.m: Created this function. 

2002-08-13  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-39

	* src/absorption.cc: Fixed bug reported by Thomas. The local copy
	of the frequency grid was initialized only once. But it was
	gradually destroyed in the case of lineshape with cutoff, because
	the cutoff frequency was added in different places for different
	lines. The only way to fix the bug was to copy the frequency grid
	inside the line loop. This adds some overhead, but the computation
	with cutoff should be still much faster than without.

	Wow, it took me a while to find this one! The absorption part
	sucks, good that we have to redo this in a clean way for ARTS-1-1.

	Incidentally, lineshapes with cutoff only work correctly if the
	frequency grid is sorted (duplicate values allowed). I have put in
	an appropriate runtime error check now.

2002-07-25  Oliver Lemke  <olemke@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-38
	
	* src/parser.cc (is_whitespace, eat_whitespace): Added backslash r
	as whitespace. Fixes bug which crashed arts when reading dos style
	control files under unix.

2002-07-17  Patrick Eriksson  <patrick@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-37

	* src/m_wfs.cc (kFrequencyOffSet): Added calculation of WF for 
	frequency off-sets (a constant shift of all frequencies in f_mono).
	The WSM is kFrequencyOffSet.

	* ami/arts/arts.m: This function now uses more elaborated ways to call
	arts from Matlab for Unix and DOS/Windows. The return argument from
	arts is now catched for those platforms and a Matlab error is given
	if there is an arts error.

2002-07-01  Carlos Jimenez  <jimenez@rss.chalmers.se>

	* arts-1-0-36

	* ami/general/whoami modified to allow identification of
	Sun computers 'computer=SOL2'

2002-06-29  Stefan Buehler  <sbuehler@uni-bremen.de>

	* arts-1-0-35

	* src/m_abs.cc (xsec_per_tgAddLines): Suppressed output of all
	transitions to do to out3. This takes longer than the calculation
	itself, if you calculate with the entire HITRAN database!

